    {"index":3,"name":"Assisted Pistol Squats","primary_muscle":"quadriceps","other_muscles":["hamstrings","glutes"],"image_url":"https://d2l9nsnmtah87f.cloudfront.net/exercise-thumbnails/23751201-Single-Leg-Squat-with-Support-(female)_Thighs_thumbnail_@3x.jpg","instructions":"1. Stand next to a squat rack and grab it with one hand for balance.\n2. Lift one foot off the floor and raise the leg a few inches forward.\n3. Engage your abs, bring your shoulders back, and take a breath.\n4. Squat by bending your knee and moving the opposite leg forward.\n5. Descend as much as possible and push through the heel to lift yourself as you exhale.\n6. Once finished training one leg, repeat on the opposite side.\n"},
